main event: On October 17, 1952, two objects were observed flying over Killeen, Texas, in a 'duck-like' formation with lights, before suddenly disappearing.
interesting points: Observers described the objects as flying at high speeds, with the ability to disappear abruptly,The sighting was reported by reliable observers, specifically clergymen,The objects were seen moving in the southwest to northeast direction,No correlation was found between the UFO sightings and weather balloons released in the area,Local residents reported seeing groups of 4 to 8 bright lights moving at high altitudes around 2000 to 5000 feet.
